President Obama has sent his congratulations to King Bhumibol Adulyadej and the people of Thailand on the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the King's accession to the throne. The President praised the King's leadership and his contributions to strengthening the bonds between the United States and Thailand. He also highlighted the King's role in promoting peace and prosperity in the Asia-Pacific region. As the only reigning monarch born in the United States, the King has a special connection with the American people. The President expressed his hope for continued cooperation between the US and Thailand to address regional and global challenges and enhance mutual prosperity.